<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Khmer Rouge kill 26 in Cambodia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PHNOM PENH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SUSPECTED Khmer Rouge guerrillas killed 26 people and wounded 20 in a rifle
and rocket attack on a village video hall in central Cambodia, aUnited
Nations official said yesterday, Reuter reports from Phnom Penh.
One attacker was also killed. It was the third massacre within three weeks
believed to have been carried out by the group responsible for the murder of
over 1m Cambodians. All the villagers were ethnic Khmers and unarmed
civilians.
At least 10 attackers fired four rockets and automatic weapons in Snau
village, in the Kompong Svay district of Kompong Thom province.
The country had appeared to be heading towards peace after the signing of an
agreement in Paris in October 1991, formally ending 13 years of civil war
among four rival factions.
But thousands of ethnic Vietnamese are fleeing their homes along the Tonle
Sap (Great Lake) to escape violence, some aiming to leave Cambodia
altogether. At least 103 ethnic Vietnamese have been murdered since the
Paris pact was signed.
</TEXT>
