<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Swedes in key vote over cuts
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Sweden's minority centre-right government faces a crucial parliamentary vote
today on cutting unemployments benefits, after talks with the opposition
Social Democrats on the issue collapsed. writes Christopher Brown-Humes in
Stockholm.
If the government loses, an early general election is likely. The populist
New Democracy party, which holds the balance of power, has not said how it
will vote.
</TEXT>
