<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Lisbon broker to face charges
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Portugal's former leading stockbroker, Mr Pedro Caldeira, who fled the
country leaving millions of dollars of debts in his wake, was extradited
back to Lisbon yesterday from the US, Reuter reports from Lisbon .
He faces charges of siphoning off Esc440m (Pounds 2m) from his Lisbon firm
of stockbrokers, Pedro Caldeira Sociedade Corretora, and failing to pay
millions of dollars owed to a bank and several other creditors.
