<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Italy's inflation at 4.2 per cent
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT GRAHAM
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Italy's inflation in March dropped to an annualised rate of 4.2 per cent,
the lowest since spring 1987, writes Robert Graham in Rome.
According to figures from Istat, the official statistics institute, prices
in March rose only 0.2 per cent. As yet the effects of the 30 per cent
devaluation of the lira against its main trading currencies has not been
felt.
</TEXT>
