<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / German output shows fall
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ARIANE GENILLARD
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BONN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Industrial output in west Germany fell 1 per cent in February after a modest
improvement in January, according to official figures published yesterday,
writes Ariane Genillard in Bonn.
The sharpest fall was recorded in consumer products where output was 2.5 per
cent lower than in January. Output in the west German construction industry,
which until last month showed growth, fell by 2 per cent.
</TEXT>
