<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / Paris and Bonn get set to do business
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MR Alain Juppe, the new French foreign minister, has announced plans to
travel to Bonn on Monday for a meeting with Mr Klaus Kinkel, his German
counterpart.
The news of the foreign ministers' meeting followed the announcement that Mr
Edouard Balladur, the new prime minister, would meet Mr Helmut Kohl, the
German chancellor, in Bonn on April 22.
Mr Balladur is anxious for his administration to forge close links with the
Germans on monetary issues. He also hopes to secure Germany's support on
strategic matters, notably France's objections to the European Community's
agricultural reforms and the present EC stance on farming in the Gatt
negotiations.
Meanwhile, Mr Juppe will meet Mr Douglas Hurd, the British foreign secretary
in Paris today. The meeting follows stiff protests from the UK government
about last Sunday's clash between French fishermen and a Royal Navy patrol
boat off the Channel Islands.
</TEXT>
