<HEADLINE>
FT  02 APR 93 / World News in Brief: Dollar falls against DM
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The dollar fell sharply against the D-Mark after the release of weaker than
expected US indicators. It bottomed out in London at DM1.5958, recovering to
close at DM1.5995, more than 1 1/4 pfennigs down. It closed in New York at
DM1.592. Sterling gained 2 cents to Dollars 1.5255 in London, and rose to
Dollars 1.53 in New York. Pressure on the dollar continued this morning,
with the US currency hitting a record low of Y113.65 shortly after the Tokyo
opening.
