FT  01 APR 93 / International Company News in Brief: Getz Bros acquires
Agroker
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NICHOLAS DENTON
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUDAPEST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Getz Bros, the international distributor and marketer indirectly owned by
the Pritzker family of the US, yesterday acquired Agroker, a leading
Hungarian wholesaler of agricultural machinery and chemicals, writes
Nicholas Denton in Budapest.
Getz, a subsidiary of the Pritzkers' diversified Marmon Group, took an 82.9
per cent stake in Agroker for an undisclosed sum.
Getz, whose activity has centred on east Asia, said it planned to expand
into both eastern and western Europe from a base in Hungary.
Yesterday's acquisition complements Getz's earlier purchase of
Intercooperation, a Hungarian trading company.
That transaction, made in 1989, is believed to have been the first outright
western acquisition of an eastern European state company.
