<DATELINE>
   HANOI
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A VIETNAMESE court has jailed eight anti-government intellectuals for up to
20 years after a two-day trial, ending a case that has aroused concern in
the west, Reuter reports from Hanoi.
They pleaded guilty to 'activities aimed at overthrowing the government,'
the official Vietnam news agency (VNA) said.
The people's court in Ho Chi Minh City on Tuesday sentenced Mr Doan Viet
Hoat to 20 years in prison. Two chief associates were jailed for 16 and 12
years. Five others convicted of belonging to an organisation called Freedom
Forum were jailed for between eight months and seven years.
