<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
CRISIS CONDITIONS in the wool market were underlined this week when the
Australian Wool Corporation's market indicator continued its steady fall,
beyond the low point reached when free market trade was first resumed in
February 1991. In real terms these are the lowest prices ever recorded. Weak
markets enhance the effects of recession and the indefinite absence of the
old Soviet Union countries. A prominent leader in the French wool textile
industry and director of the International Wool Secretariat has outspokenly
suggested that the stockpile in Australia should be destroyed, as the only
way to allow prices to rise.
