FT  01 APR 93 / International Company News: Honeywell in aircraft computer
deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By LOUISE KEHOE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SAN FRANCISCO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
APPLE Macintosh personal computers will find their way into the cockpits of
commercial aircraft as a result of an agreement reached between Apple and
Honeywell's Commercial Flight Systems Group.
Under the deal, Honeywell will develop an electronic library which will
provide flight crews with multi-media versions of maintenance and operation
manuals that incorporate video, graphics and sound as well as text.
Honeywell will also make a 'ruggedised' version of Apple's
recently-introduced Macintosh Quadra 800 high-performance PC for the cockpit
information system.
This is the first time Apple has licensed its Macintosh computer technology
under such an Original Equipment Manufacturer agreement and signals a new
strategy to broaden the markets for its technology.
Honeywell said it planned to provide its airline customers with an
easy-to-use information system.
The Honeywell deal is the first to be reached by New Media/New Markets, a
new group formed at Apple to focus on opportunities created by publishing,
entertainment, telecommunications, computing and consumer electronics.
