<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / UK Company News: Test case over ICI shares
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By SCHEHERAZADE DANESHKHU
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
ICI said yesterday that it was trying to clarify the legal situation
surrounding the status of shares issued as a result of its planned demerger
and the creation of Zeneca, a new publicly listed company.
Trustees with ICI shares may find that the Zeneca shares are regarded as
income of a trust rather than as capital, which will cause problems for
trustees having to balance the distribution of income for the life tenant
against the need to preserve the capital for those entitled to it after the
life tenant's death.
A test case, assisted by ICI and brought by solicitors Berwin Leighton, is
expected to be heard later this month with a judgment expected in early May.
</TEXT>
