<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / UK Company News: NatWest sued in US over dealings
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GAPPER, Banking Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
NATIONAL Westminster Bank is being sued in US federal courts over stock
dealings on behalf of Phar-Mor, a drugstore chain which went into Chapter 11
bankruptcy in August, it was disclosed in the bank's annual report.
It is being sued for allegedly placing Dollars 112m (Pounds 79m) of common
stock on behalf of Phar-Mor which should have been registered. NatWest is
also said to have made misrepresentations in connection with the sale of
Dollars 24m of stock.
The bank said it was contesting the allegations and did not believe they
would have a material effect on net assets. It also disclosed that it had
received claims in connection with the collapse of Maxwell Communication
Corporation.
The highest paid UK director was Mr Richard Goeltz, the chief financial
officer, who received a total of Pounds 383,900, including Pounds 99,074 of
expenses incurred by the bank in his move from New York to London.
</TEXT>
