FT  01 APR 93 / Letter: Lean burn ignored
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr IVOR BUFTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Concluding his article, 'The lion sleeps tonight' (March 26), Joe
Rogaly assets, gratuitously, that the government is 'running down an
industry that, on environmental grounds, should be written off by the turn
of the century'.
This completely overlooks the existence of the technology to burn coal much
more efficiently to produce electricity, with significantly reduced
environmental damage.
Practical implementation of this was blocked during the 1980s by the
government's refusal to authorise the very modest finance for 'lean burn'.
Ivor Bufton,
