<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / People: Non-executive directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Argyll, the UK retailing group, has appointed two non-exec-utive directors
following the retirement from the board of Sir Cranley Onslow MP, a former
chairman of the 1922 committee, and a non-executive director since 1983.
The appointments increase non-executive representation on the board from
four to five.
Ann Burdus (above left), 49, joins the board from today, and will join
Argyll's audit and remuneration committees. A well-known personality in the
advertising world, she joined Ogilvy, Benson &amp; Mather in 1961, before moving
to McCann &amp; Co where she rose to be chairman 1979-81. She is a former
chairman of the Advertising Association, and is a member of the Top Salaries
Review Board. She is also a director of Dawson International.
Neville Bain (right), 52, chief executive of Coats Viyella, joins on May 1.
Before joining Coats in 1989 he worked for 29 years in the food industry
with Cadbury Schweppes, where he was latterly finance director and deputy
chief executive. He will chair Argyll's audit committee, and join the
remuneration committee.
</TEXT>
