FT  01 APR 93 / Parliament and Politics: Support for recycling schemes
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government yesterday announced the allocation of Pounds 15m in
supplementary credit approvals for recycling schemes run by local
authorities in England.
Mr David Maclean, environment minister, said priority had been given to
schemes to collect waste oil and ozone-depleting CFCs.
In a written reply, he said credit approvals had been authorised for 161
authorities covering 307 schemes, ranging from home composting projects to
mini-recycling centres.
Supplementary credit approvals allow local authorities to borrow for
specific types of capital investment, beyond the limit set by their basic
credit approval.
