<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / Possible face lift for Wimbledon
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wimbledon, home of tennis stars past and present such as Michael Stich
(left) and Rod Laver could have a face-lift if proposals unveiled yesterday
by the All-England Lawn Tennis Club are approved. The plans, by consultants
Building Design Partnership, aim to improve facilities for spectators,
players and officials.
Under the proposals Number One court will be demolished to make way for a
facilities building, and a new show court will be built. Planning permission
is being sought and work could begin by 1995. The project will be financed
by the issue of debentures.
</TEXT>
