FT  01 APR 93 / Warning as more Daf jobs go
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
RELUCTANCE by some component manufacturers to keep supplying the Leyland Daf
truck plant at Leyland, Lancashire, is again threatening efforts to sell it
as a going concern, its administrative receivers warned yesterday.
The warning came as a further 349 Leyland Daf workers were made redundant.
Most of the redundancies - 273 - were at the Leyland trucks plant, leaving a
workforce of 273. The remaining 76 jobs went at the Albion axle plant,
Glasgow, leaving a workforce of 342.
