<HEADLINE>
FT  01 APR 93 / VAT 'most resented tax'
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
VALUE added tax imposes the most resented tax burden on small businesses,
according to research for Barclays Bank.
The burden of VAT lies not so much in its financial cost but in its impact
on a business's cashflow and time taken in administration, the research
showed. Sixty per cent of the 200 small businesses surveyed said VAT was the
main cause of cashflow management problems, while 62 per cent said it
required more administration than any other tax.
